## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent data, as much of the accessible information is from studies conducted several years ago. Additionally, the complexity of marine ecosystems means that the full impact of pollution is challenging to quantify. Further research and updated data are necessary to provide a more comprehensive understanding of the current state of pollution in the East China Sea.

